# commitEditing

**Instance Method**

Returns whether the receiver was able to commit any pending edits.

## Declaration

```swift
- (BOOL) commitEditing;
```

## Return Value

[doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/YES] if the changes were successfully applied to the model, [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/NO] otherwise.

## Discussion

A commit is denied if the receiver fails to apply the changes to the model object, perhaps due to a validation error.

## Related Documentation

- **discardEditing**: Causes the receiver to discard any changes, restoring the previous values.
